body: @yufenglee: Thank you for the help. This resolved my issue.

In the previous version, we could save the model with a custom OP "TRTEngine", and that's very useful when we want to speed up the model loading while the device will never be changed. So I was wondering why this feature was removed?
@yufenglee When using TensorRT, the loading process is very slow. So now how can I speed it up just like the TF-TRT static model?

Hi @yufenglee , I am getting the same error for a VAE model - [here](https://cern.ch/geant4-data/datasets/examples/extended/parameterisations/Par04/Generator.onnx) but for C++ API when using TensorRT, **the error is thrown when creating a session**. In C++ API, I am able to use CUDA EP and for python, I am able to use TensorRT as well.

I have built a custom onnxruntime environment containing oneDNN, OpenVINO, CUDA and TensorRT providers. To create this environment, I had to mix and merge different dockerfiles and solved dependency issues whereever encountered. The Dockerfile is at end.

The main onnxruntime build command - 
```
./build.sh --config Release --update --build --parallel --build_wheel --build_shared_lib --build_dir /opt/onnxruntime/build \
    	--cmake_extra_defines CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/opt/onnxruntime/install ONNXRUNTIME_VERSION=$(cat ./VERSION_NUMBER) 'CMAKE_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES=37;50;52;60;61;70;75;80;86' \
    	--use_dnnl \
    	--use_openvino ${OPENVINO_DEVICE}\
    	--use_cuda --cuda_home /usr/local/cuda --cudnn_home /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/ \
    	--use_tensorrt --tensorrt_home /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/
```

Python API:
```python
import onnxruntime as ort
import numpy as np

sess = ort.InferenceSession(/path/to/model, providers=["TensorrtExecutionProvider", "CUDAExecutionProvider"])

dum_in = np.random.randint(10, size=[1]+[sess.get_inputs()[0].shape[1]])
dum_in_name = sess.get_inputs()[0].name

dum_res = sess.run(None, {dum_in_name: dum_in.astype(np.float32)})

```

C++ API:
```c
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>

   /// Pointer to the ONNX inference session
   std::unique_ptr<Ort::Session> fSession;
   /// ONNX settings
   Ort::SessionOptions fSessionOptions;

   auto envLocal = std::make_unique<Ort::Env>(ORT_LOGGING_LEVEL_WARNING, "ENV");
   fEnv          = std::move(envLocal);

   // Creating a OrtApi Class variable for getting access to C api, necessary for CUDA and TensorRT EP.
   const auto& ortApi = Ort::GetApi();
   OrtTensorRTProviderOptionsV2* fTrtOptions = nullptr;
   Ort::ThrowOnError(ortApi.CreateTensorRTProviderOptions(&fTrtOptions));
   std::vector<const char*> trt_keys{
      "device_id",
      "trt_max_workspace_size",
      "trt_max_partition_iterations",
      "trt_min_subgraph_size",
      "trt_fp16_enable",
      "trt_int8_enable",
      "trt_int8_use_native_calibration_table",
      "trt_engine_cache_enable",
      "trt_engine_cache_path",
      "trt_dump_subgraphs",
   };
   std::vector<const char*> trt_values{
      "0",                          // device_id
      "2147483648",                 // trt_max_workspace_size
      "10",                         // trt_max_partition_iterations
      "5",                          // trt_min_subgraph_size
      "0",                          // trt_fp16_enable
      "1",                          // trt_int8_enable
      "1",                          // trt_int8_use_native_calibration_table 
      "1",                          // trt_engine_cache_enable
      "/opt/trt/geant4/cache",      // trt_engine_cache_path
      "1"                           // trt_dump_subgraphs   
   };
   Ort::ThrowOnError(ortApi.UpdateTensorRTProviderOptions(fTrtOptions, trt_keys.data(), trt_values.data(), trt_keys.size()));
   Ort::ThrowOnError(ortApi.SessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_TensorRT_V2(fSessionOptions, fTrtOptions));
  
   OrtCUDAProviderOptionsV2* fCudaOptions = nullptr;
   Ort::ThrowOnError(ortApi.CreateCUDAProviderOptions(&fCudaOptions));
   std::vector<const char*> cuda_keys{
      "device_id",
      "gpu_mem_limit", 
      "arena_extend_strategy", 
      "cudnn_conv_algo_search", 
      "do_copy_in_default_stream", 
      "cudnn_conv_use_max_workspace", 
      //"cudnn_conv1d_pad_to_nc1d"
   };
   std::vector<const char*> cuda_values{
      "0",                  // device_id
      "2147483648",         // gpu_mem_limit
      "kSameAsRequested",   // arena_extend_strategy
      "DEFAULT",            // cudnn_conv_algo_search
      "1",                  // do_copy_in_default_stream
      "1",                  // cudnn_conv_use_max_workspace
      //"1"                   // cudnn_conv1d_pad_to_nc1d
   };
   Ort::ThrowOnError(ortApi.UpdateCUDAProviderOptions(fCudaOptions, cuda_keys.data(), cuda_values.data(), cuda_keys.size()));
   Ort::ThrowOnError(ortApi.SessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_CUDA_V2(fSessionOptions, fCudaOptions));

   auto sessionLocal = std::make_unique<Ort::Session>(*fEnv, modelPath, fSessionOptions);
   fSession          = std::move(sessionLocal);
   .
   .
   .
   .
   .
   return 0
}
```

```Dockerfile
ARG TRT_CONTAINER_VERSION=21.12

LABEL description="This is the dev image for Intel(R) Distribution of OpenVINO(TM) toolkit on Ubuntu 20.04 LTS"
LABEL vendor="Intel Corporation"

WORKDIR /

SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-xo", "pipefail", "-c"]

ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive

    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends ${LGPL_DEPS} && \

    if [ "$INSTALL_SOURCES" = "yes" ]; then \
      sed -Ei 's/# deb-src /deb-src /' /etc/apt/sources.list && \

	  dpkg --get-selections | grep -v deinstall | awk '{print $1}' > all_packages.txt && \

WORKDIR ${INTEL_OPENVINO_DIR}/licensing
```
